3, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"William de Alfreton was born in 1148, in Belper, Derbyshire, England as the son of Robert de Alfreton. He married Idonea Blackwell about 1170, in Nottinghamshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 2 daughters. He died in 1185, in Nottinghamshire, England, at the age of 37."},"et":{"1148–1185":"1148–1185","1152–Female":"1152–Surnud","1148–1194":"1148–1194","1170–1225":"1170–1225","1176–1215":"1176–1215","1162–1228":"1162–1228","1117–1170":"1117–1170","about 1162":"umbes 1162","about 1170":"umbes 1170","1176":"1176","1185":"1185","1152":"1152","1162":"1162","1194":"1194","1170":"1170","1228":"1228","1117":"1117","1215":"1215","1148":"1148","5 April 1170":"5. aprill 1170","1225":"1225","about 1176":"umbes 1176","Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, England","Belper, Derbyshire, England":"Belper, Derbyshire, England","Wellbeck, Nottinghamshire, England":"Nottinghamshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Hagnaby, Lincolnshire, England":"Hagnaby, Lincolnshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Alfreton, Derbyshire, England":"Alfreton, Derbyshire, England"},"fi":{"1148–1185":"1148–1185","1152–Female":"1152–Kuollut","1148–1194":"1148–1194","1170–1225":"1170–1225","1176–1215":"1176–1215","1162–1228":"1162–1228","1117–1170":"1117–1170","about 1162":"noin 1162","about 1170":"noin 1170","1176":"1176"